               </msIdentifier>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>Extended list of land from Panopolis (modern name: Akhmim), Egypt, written on papyrus. Land is presumably owned by the family of Ammon, the well-known scholastikos, or lawyer. The holdings are in the various divisions of the Panopolite Nome and are often quite small. Many numbered plots occur. Lists tenants with some of the holdings. Papyrus belongs to archive of Ammon. Recto has a private letter in Greek (P.Duk.inv. 177 R)</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 24.5 x 77.5 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">128 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 1 cm.; lower margin of 1.5 cm.; left margin of 3 cm.; right margin of 10 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 177 V was formerly P.Duk.inv. G 177 V</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 177 V joins P.Koln inv. 4534 and 4538, which have been on indefinite loan to Duke University since 1986</note>
                     <note type="general">Written in five columns across the fibers on the verso in Ammon's informal hand; some marginal annotations in between the columns, two sets of annotations in the right margin written with another pen; written along the fibers on the recto in Ammon's careful hand</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
